{
  "texts": [
    "Items are designed to capture how unpredictable, uncontrollable, and overloaded participants find their lives.",
    "Items are rated on a 5-point Likert-type scale ranging from 0 to 4, and higher scores indicate greater stress.",
    "All items are summed to create a total score.",
    "The PSS-10 has shown good internal consistency and demonstrated expected correlations with a variety of constructs [96].",
    "The PSS-10 demonstrated good reliability in the present sample (α Pre = 0.81; α Post = 0.81; α 3-Month Follow-up = 0.90; α 6-Month Follow-up = 0.85).The Oldenburg Burnout Inventory (OLBI; [97,98]) is a 16-item measure of burnout that assesses exhaustion and disengagement from work."
  ]
}